title: Jason Priestley: "It's nobody's business" whether I hooked up wi
text:
By Liz Raftery, Jason Priestley won't be following Tori Spelling 's lead in spilling details about the offscreen relationship they allegedly had when filming Beverly Hills, 90210 .
After Spelling took a lie detector test for Lifetime this weekend and admitted that she and Priestley had a "fling" one summer while filming the show, fans asked Priestley via Twitter to confirm her comments.
"I'm not getting into this... It's nobody's business," he responded .
(Spelling also confirmed that she and co-star Brian Austin Green were romantically involved at one point, and that she once got a kiss from Luke Perry .)
While interacting with fans on Twitter, Priestley claimed that he didn't watch either Spelling's lie detector segment or Lifetime's The Unauthorized Beverly Hills, 90210 Story , but clarified that he has no negative feelings towards the original series.
I didn't watch it... Why would I? https://t.co/dAfi7XjMA4
— Jason Priestley (@Jason_Priestley) October 4, 2015
I'm actually feeling a little nostalgic today... That show was quite an experience... I owe it a lot... https://t.co/rv2G7P8yXd
— Jason Priestley (@Jason_Priestley) October 4, 2015
